Governor Samuel Ortom of Benue State on Wednesday disclosed that he tested negative for the COVID-19 virus.  The Governor said this while addressing journalists at the new banquet hall of Government House, Makurdi. He appreciated the people of the state, his friends and supporters across the country for their prayers during the period of self-isolation. Ortom also thanked his deputy, Benson Abounu, and urged the people of the state to adhere strictly to the COVID-19 protocols.  Source By Philip Dzeremo Makurdi - The Benue Government on Saturday announced the state’s first case of COVID-19 in Makurdi, the state capital. Gov Samuel Ortom made the announcement at a press briefing in Makurdi shortly after an emergency meeting of the State Emergency Response Team (SERT), on COVID-19. Ortom said… In "News" Governor Samuel Ortom of Benue, has called for 30 days of fasting and intense prayers by the Benue people to seek God’s favour in combating the renewed herdsmen attack in some parts of the state. Ortom made this call on Thursday in Makurdi while interacting with newsmen on the occasion… In "News" Benue Governor Samuel Ortom has tested positive for COVID-19. His Chief Press Secretary, Terver Akase, announced this on Wednesday. Akase, in a statement made available to journalists in Makurdi, said: “The latest result of his (governor Ortom) COVID-19 test has returned positive. “This follows the test results of most of… In "Politics"